100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 20, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva to address pressing global issues, emphasizing the need for disarmament and international cooperation. In the United States, the trial of teacher John T. Scopes continued, drawing national attention as it challenged the teaching of evolution in schools. Meanwhile, political tensions escalated in Europe, particularly with ongoing disputes in the Balkans, raising concerns about stability in the region.
